# StyleSwipe Core

## Implementation Specs

Use [PLAN.md](PLAN.md) and [lowLevelDoc.md](lowLevelDoc.md) as the authoritative implementation specs. Reference section numbers when implementing features.

## Conventions

- **IDs:** UUID v4 for all entity IDs
- **Timestamps:** ISO8601 in UTC
- **Tags:** Lowercase only; must come from the taxonomy in lowLevelDoc §2.1 (style, color, material, occasion, category, fit, pattern)

## Environment

- **Client:** `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` (from `.env`)
- **Edge Functions:** `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (Supabase secrets)
- Never put service role key or other secrets in client code
- Never commit `.env`; use `.env.example` with placeholders

## Project Layout

- `app/` — Expo Router screens (file-based routing)
- `contexts/` — React contexts (e.g. AuthContext)
- `lib/` — Shared utilities, Supabase client
- `supabase/functions/` — Edge Functions
- `supabase/functions/_shared/` — Shared Edge Function modules (cors.ts, tagScoring.ts)
